# .dockerignore — Suite-Shavi Docker build context exclusions
#
# Purpose: Exclude files that are not needed in the Docker build context,
# particularly nested node_modules that would shadow root-level generated
# Prisma client and cause runtime type/value mismatch.
#
# Evidence: Gate 10 workspace reconciliation — modules/platform-admin/node_modules/.prisma/client
# was a stale generated client (no InviteStatus). After COPY . . in Dockerfile, it shadowed
# the correctly-generated /app/node_modules/.prisma/client at runtime, causing silent startup crash.
# Node.js resolves .prisma/client relative to @prisma/client's location, finds the nested stale
# copy first, returns undefined for InviteStatus.invited etc.

# Exclude nested platform-admin node_modules (npm ci at root installs everything needed)
modules/platform-admin/node_modules/

# Exclude local dist output (compiled fresh in Docker build)
dist/

# Exclude development/test artifacts
*.test.mjs
forensic-*/
node_error*.txt
node_output*.txt
variables.txt
